# EKS kubectl Context Commands - DevOps Engineer

## Complete Stepwise Workflow (All-in-One)

```bash
# STEP 1: Check available contexts
kubectl config get-contexts

# STEP 2: View current context
kubectl config current-context

# STEP 3: Configure EKS cluster access
aws eks update-kubeconfig --region <region> --name <cluster-name>

# STEP 4: Switch to EKS context
kubectl config use-context <eks-context-name>

# STEP 5: Set default namespace
kubectl config set-context --current --namespace=<namespace>

# STEP 6: Verify configuration
kubectl config view --minify

# STEP 7: Test cluster connection
kubectl cluster-info && kubectl get nodes

# STEP 8: Verify pods and services
kubectl get pods,svc --all-namespaces
